HEADWORD: Standpoint
<hw>Stand"point`</hw> <pr>(-point`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>standpunkt</ets>.]</ety> <def>A fixed point or station; a basis or
fundamental principle; a position from which objects or principles are
viewed, and according to which they are compared and judged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

